Explain:-
strings data.txt - Reads the contents of the file.
| - The pipe operator takes the output of the first command and passes it as input 
    to the next.
tr 'A-Za-z' 'N-ZA-Mn-za-m' - This translates every character in the first set (A-Za-z') to its corresponding character in the second 
                             set (N-ZA-Mn-za-m), effectively shifting them back by 13 positions.

